  "transcript": [
    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 3.84,
      "text": "This is the LibriVox recording. All LibriVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 4.78,
      "end": 8.66,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibriVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 10.16,
      "end": 15.98,
      "text": "Esab's Fable, the Swollen Fox. Read by Patrick McNeil, Bakersfield, California.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 17.86,
      "end": 21.74,
      "text": "A hungry fox found in a hollow tree, a quantity of bread and meat,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 22.22,
      "end": 24.2,
      "text": "which some shepherds had placed there against their return.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 25.22,
      "end": 29.88,
      "text": "Delighted with his find, he slipped in through the narrow aperture and greedily devoured it all.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 30.52,
      "end": 35.24,
      "text": "But when he tried to get out again, he found himself so swollen after his big meal that he",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 35.24,
      "end": 39.5,
      "text": "could not squeeze through the hole and fell to whining and groaning over his misfortune.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 40.56,
      "end": 44.92,
      "text": "Another fox, happening to pass that way, came and asked him what the matter was.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 45.34,
      "end": 50.12,
      "text": "And on learning the state of the case said, well, my friend, I see nothing for it,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 50.28,
      "end": 53.2,
      "text": "but for you to stay where you are till you shrink to your former size.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 53.2,
      "end": 57.64,
      "text": "You'll get out then easily enough. End of Fable.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
